sergey d odintsov icrea ieec barcelona introduction to modified gravities and gravitational dark energy abstract we revie page 1 sergey d odintsov icrea ieec barcelona introduction to modified gravities and gravitational dark energy abstract we review the various models of modified gravity f r gravity string inspired dilaton gravity modified gauss bonnett gravity etc it is shown that some of these models may comply with solar system tests it is demonstrated that they provide gravitational alternative for dark energy thanks to terms which grow with decreasing curvature they successfully describe cosmological constant quintessence or phantom cosmic acceleration as well as transition from deceleration to acceleration the relation of such models with scalar tensor gravity as well as their representation as inhomogeneous equation of state is also reviewed
